<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="737" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2734: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-10T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 10,
                                        1923—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>36. Referring to your despatches and others from the Military Governor on
                            recent smuggling of arms, please report by telegraph whether indications
                            of smuggling continue. You are authorized, in your discretion, to ask
                            Provisional Government what measures have been taken in this regard.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>